<HI>She had no &s;ooner &s;aid the&s;e words,
but &s;he went out of the Room, lea|ving
the Duke alone in a very deep
Study, and not a little vex'd at him|&s;elf,
for having &s;aid more than he
&s;hould have done; for whil&s;t he
thought to put upon the Dutche&s;s,
in relating to her on$ of the Count's
<PB N="133" REF="137">
Gallantries, and reproaching her for
hers, he was catch'd in the Snare
him&s;elf; &s;o that he was &s;carce in a
